UID:step1-jun-19@bakesiga.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260511T235901Z
DTSTART;TZID=Africa/Kampala:20260619T190000
DTEND;TZID=Africa/Kampala:20260619T203000
SUMMARY:USMLE Step 1 · Epidemiology & Biostatistics · Day 1: Study designs
 \, levels of evidence\, and diagnostic testing
DESCRIPTION:Observational vs experimental designs: case reports\, case ser
 ies\, cross-sectional\, case-control\, cohort\, RCTs\, meta-analyses. Leve
 ls of evidence pyramid. Clinical trial phases (I–IV). Diagnostic test char
 acteristics: 2×2 tables\, sensitivity\, specificity\, positive and negativ
 e predictive values (PPV/NPV)\, likelihood ratios\, prevalence effects\, R
 OC curves\, pre- and post-test probability\, Bayes' theorem. Screening pri
 nciples and worked examples (troponins\, D-dimer\, common screening tests)
 . UWorld questions.\n\nFirst Aid: 256–262\n\nJoin Zoom: https://duke.zoom.
 us/j/96991939005\n\nMeeting ID: 969 9193 9005\n\nDashboard: https://bakesi
 ga.github.io/usmle-dashboard
URL:https://duke.zoom.us/j/96991939005
LOCATION:https://duke.zoom.us/j/96991939005
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT15M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:USMLE Step 1 · Epidemiology & Biostatistics · Day 1: Study des
 igns\, levels of evidence\, and diagnostic testing
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
