UID:step1-jun-20@bakesiga.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260511T235901Z
DTSTART;TZID=Africa/Kampala:20260620T190000
DTEND;TZID=Africa/Kampala:20260620T203000
SUMMARY:USMLE Step 1 · Epidemiology & Biostatistics · Day 2: Quantifying r
 isk\, demographic transitions\, and survival analysis
DESCRIPTION:Risk quantification: incidence\, prevalence\, relative risk (R
 R)\, odds ratio (OR)\, absolute risk reduction (ARR)\, number needed to tr
 eat (NNT) and NNH\, attributable risk. Demographic transition theory and t
 he epidemiologic transition through the stages of population health. Survi
 val analysis: Kaplan-Meier curves\, log-rank test\, Cox proportional hazar
 ds / hazard ratios\, censoring. UWorld questions.\n\nFirst Aid: 260–263\n\
 nJoin Zoom: https://duke.zoom.us/j/96991939005\n\nMeeting ID: 969 9193 900
 5\n\nDashboard: https://bakesiga.github.io/usmle-dashboard
URL:https://duke.zoom.us/j/96991939005
LOCATION:https://duke.zoom.us/j/96991939005
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT15M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:USMLE Step 1 · Epidemiology & Biostatistics · Day 2: Quantifyi
 ng risk\, demographic transitions\, and survival analysis
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:step1-jun-21@bakesiga.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260511T235901Z
DTSTART;TZID=Africa/Kampala:20260621T190000
DTEND;TZID=Africa/Kampala:20260621T203000
SUMMARY:USMLE Step 1 · Epidemiology & Biostatistics · Day 3: Bias\, confou
 nding\, and effect modification
DESCRIPTION:Types of bias and how to minimize them — selection bias\, reca
 ll bias\, observer/measurement bias\, lead-time bias\, length-time bias\, 
 attrition bias\, Hawthorne effect\, publication bias. Confounding: definit
 ion\, recognition\, control strategies (randomization\, restriction\, matc
 hing\, stratification\, multivariable adjustment). Effect modification (in
 teraction) — how it differs from confounding and how to detect it. UWorld 
 questions.\n\nFirst Aid: 263–264\n\nJoin Zoom: https://duke.zoom.us/j/9699
 1939005\n\nMeeting ID: 969 9193 9005\n\nDashboard: https://bakesiga.github
 .io/usmle-dashboard
URL:https://duke.zoom.us/j/96991939005
LOCATION:https://duke.zoom.us/j/96991939005
BEGIN:VALARM
TRIGGER:-PT15M
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:USMLE Step 1 · Epidemiology & Biostatistics · Day 3: Bias\, co
 nfounding\, and effect modification
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:step1-jun-22@bakesiga.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260511T235901Z
DTSTART;TZID=Africa/Kampala:20260622T190000
DTEND;TZID=Africa/Kampala:20260622T203000
SUMMARY:USMLE Step 1 · Epidemiology & Biostatistics · Day 4: Statistical d
 istributions\, statistical testing\, and confidence intervals
DESCRIPTION:Statistical distributions — normal/Gaussian\, binomial\, Poiss
 on\, t-distribution\; measures of central tendency and dispersion\; standa
 rd error vs standard deviation. Statistical testing: hypothesis testing\, 
 p-values\, type I (α) and type II (β) errors\, statistical power. Confiden
 ce intervals — construction and interpretation. Common tests by data type 
 (t-test\, paired t\, ANOVA\, chi-squared\, Fisher's exact\, correlation an
 d regression). Interpreting forest plots and meta-analyses. UWorld questio
 ns.\n\nFirst Aid: 265–266\n\nJoin Zoom: https://duke.zoom.us/j/96991939005
